Package: shinyData
Type: Package
Title: A GUI application for interactive data analysis, visualization and presentation
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: "Yindeng Jiang <jiangyindeng@gmail.com> [aut, cre]"
Description:
  shinyData is an easy to use tool for interactive data analysis, visualization and presentation.
  It leverages the power of R and its vast collection of packages to allow users to efficiently perform common
  data tasks, such as slicing and dicing, aggregation, pattern recognition, visualization and more.
  Almost no knowledge of R programming is required to use shinyData.
Depends: R (>= 3.1.2)
Imports:
  shiny (>= 0.11.1),
  ggplot2 (>= 1.0.0), Hmisc (>= 3.14-6),
  uuid (>= 0.1-1),
  tables (>= 0.7.79),
  png (>= 0.1-7), data.table (>= 1.9.4),
  Cairo (>= 1.5-6),
  knitr (>= 1.9), rmarkdown (>= 0.4.2)
Suggests:
  extrafont (>= 0.17)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
URL: https://github.com/yindeng/shinyData
BugReports: https://github.com/yindeng/shinyData/issues
